  </div>
</section>

<!-- SECTION 2: WHY THIS AREA -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2ead4); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#b98229; margin-bottom:1rem;">Local Expertise</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:400; font-variation-settings:'opsz' 32; line-height:1.2; color:#191817; margin-bottom:1.75rem;">Large blocks and quiet residential living at an affordable southern entry point.</h2>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Larapinta sits approximately 19 kilometres south of the Brisbane CBD, positioned in the outer southern corridor alongside Heathwood, Algester, Calamvale and Parkinson. It is a suburb defined by larger residential blocks, established gardens and a quiet character that distinguishes it from the denser estate pockets of its immediate neighbours. Families who have been priced out of Algester and Calamvale look to Larapinta as the next step: more land, comparable schooling access and a community feel that rewards long-term ownership.
    </p>
<!-- APPRAISAL FORM -->
<div style="background:#fff; border-left:4px solid #b98229; padding:2rem 2rem 1.75rem; margin:2rem 0; border-radius:16px;">
  <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.72rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.18em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#b98229; margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Free Appraisal</p>
