</style>
<!-- END APPRAISAL FORM -->
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      I work across the outer southern corridor and understand the Larapinta buyer profile clearly. Families comparing Larapinta against Algester and Heathwood come with a pre-approval, a clear idea of what they need in block size and layout, and a price expectation formed by months of watching comparable sales. Positioning a campaign correctly against those benchmarks is what separates a result at the strong end of the range from one that sits on market.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Larapinta's larger land content is its defining asset. Properties with flat, usable blocks that can accommodate a pool, outdoor entertaining and practical backyard space attract a clear buyer premium relative to constrained or steeply sloped sites. The Logan Motorway provides straightforward southern and western corridor access, and the proximity to Calamvale's retail precinct gives the suburb a practical everyday convenience that its quiet residential character might otherwise suggest is missing.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:1.5rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #b98229; border-radius:16px;">
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.1rem; font-weight:400; color:#191817; margin-bottom:0.4rem;">Outer South Specialist</p>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:300; color:#6b6560;">Brisbane's southern family corridor</p>
